According to Hong Kong authorities, a protest might take place at Terminal 1 Hong Kong International Airport on 26 July. Vietnam Airlines and Jetstar Pacific's flights are still operating as scheduled. We recommend passengers to arrive at airport 3 hours early.
#HongKongProtest https://t.co/rHIF7rcPBd

entity.name: Thousands gather to take part in latest Hong Kong protest
entity.description: Following weeks of protests against a controversial extradition bill which would have allowed people to be sent to mainland China for trial, residents are rallying over key issues on democracy in Hong Kong. Reports suggest riot police fired tear gas to disperse protesters who defied orders by ignoring the designated finish line of an earlier rally on Sunday.
